        "\"\"\"\n",
        "================================================================================\n",
        "Chicago Trip-Level Discrete Choice Model (Logistic Regression Baseline)\n",
        "================================================================================\n",
        "PURPOSE:\n",
        "    Build a TRIP-LEVEL dataset where each row is one trip,\n",
        "    with BOTH origin and destination built environment features,\n",
        "    and fit logistic regression models for mode choice.\n",
        "\n",
        "RESEARCH DESIGN:\n",
        "    Unit of analysis:  Individual TRIPS (not persons, not OD pairs)\n",
        "    Dependent var:     Binary mode choice (e.g., transit vs. non-transit)\n",
        "    Independent vars:  Origin BE features + Destination BE features\n",
        "                       + Person/household sociodemographics\n",
        "                       + Trip-level characteristics (distance, etc.)\n",
        "    Model:             Logistic Regression\n",
        "\n",
        "REFERENCE:\n",
        "    Ha, J., Ki, D., Lee, S., & Ko, J. (2023). Mode choice and the\n",
        "    first-/last-mile burden. Transportation Research Part D, 116, 103646.\n",
        "\n",
        "KEY DIFFERENCE FROM PERSON-LEVEL PIPELINE:\n",
        "    - Person-level: aggregate all trips → one row per person\n",
        "    - Trip-level:   keep every trip → one row per trip\n",
        "    - Trip-level allows using BOTH origin AND destination features\n",
        "\n",
        "PIPELINE OVERVIEW:\n",
        "    Phase 1: Load raw survey data\n",
        "    Phase 2: Filter to Chicago residents\n",
        "    Phase 3: Build trip-level records with O/D location info\n",
        "    Phase 4: Assign O/D locations to Census Block Groups (zones)\n",
        "    Phase 5: Attach zone-level BE features to BOTH origin and destination\n",
        "    Phase 6: Attach person/household sociodemographic features\n",
        "    Phase 7: Construct dependent variables (binary mode choice)\n",
        "    Phase 8: Clean data and save\n",
        "    Phase 9: Fit logistic regression models\n",
        "================================================================================\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
